Optional suggestion: I would prefer
```suggestion
      dsimp only [flip_X_X, flip_X_d]
```
or even
```suggestion
      dsimp
```
to show that there are no missing `simp` lemmas. Similar in `totalFlipIsoX_hom_D₂` below.

Not sure if you care, but if you add the lemma
```lean
lemma flip_flip (K : HomologicalComplex₂ C c₁ c₂) : K.flip.flip = K :=
  rfl
```
to `HomologicalBicomplex.lean`, then you can avoid the `erw` here, for example by saying
```suggestion
  dsimp only [flip_X_X, total_X, Iso.symm_hom]
  rw [ιTotal_totalFlipIso_f_hom]
  dsimp only [flip_flip]
  rw [K.ιTotal_totalFlipIso_f_inv, ComplexShape.σ_symm]
```
